DIV1.P:
But when was this objected, unless the objector's principles or practices had been censured? Such Instances are rare indeed. Where this has not been the case, 'tis said,
these matters are handled in the scripture, and therefore naturally come under the consideration of those who are set apart to study and explain the scriptures, and urge the duties therein con∣tained;
but the case changes immediately, when their faults are reprehended, and the minister is tied up to the gospel doctrines of faith and repentance.—
